# 呪術廻戦 — Cursed Technique Visualizer

A browser-based hand gesture recognition system that lets you cast Jujutsu Kaisen 
techniques with real hand movements. Built with Three.js particle systems and 
MediaPipe Hands for real-time landmark detection — no backend, no ML training, 
just vanilla JS and WebGL.

## Features
- 🖐️ Real-time hand tracking via webcam (MediaPipe Hands)
- ✨ 20,000-particle GPU-accelerated system morphing between techniques
- 🎮 Gesture-based technique triggers:
  - Pinch → Hollow Purple
  - Open palm → Malevolent Shrine (Domain Expansion)
  - Peace sign variant → Infinite Void
  - Index finger → Reverse Cursed Technique: Red
- 🎨 Dynamic bloom post-processing that intensifies per technique
- 📷 Live camera feed overlay with skeleton tracking visualization

## Tech Stack
Three.js · MediaPipe Hands · WebGL · EffectComposer/UnrealBloomPass · Vanilla JS

